data.title: Great Food and Service
data.text:
I went to the Downtown Art Festival with a friend who highly recommended Emiliano's. Their Saturday brunch was still going on, and I was tempted to order the crab cakes Benedict off the brunch menu. But I went with the Portobello sandwich off the lunch menu and had no regrets. My friend went with a Cuban-style dish off the lunch menu.

Servers were very attentive and prices were quite reasonable. The only tiny drawback is that the interior is quite dark, even at midday.

data.title: Consistently excellent, fresh food
data.text: I've been to Emiliano's about 8 times over the past few months and am impressed with the consistently excellent, freshly prepared dishes.  I don't eat mammals or birds so everything I've had is either vegetarian or seafood, but all of those dishes are excellent, and the specials are consistently enticing and live up to their descriptions by the friendly and attentive wait staff.  The outdoor patio is usually where I sit as the inside is a bit cool for my liking, and fortunately in Gainesville we so often have pleasant weather for sitting in the shade.  They have a decent wine list and a great collection of beer featuring crafts from local breweries.  The prices are reasonable too and the portion sizes are perfect - not the typical American over-indulgence in terms of meal size and not the dainty gourmet portions of haute cuisine - just the right size for 2-3 tapas to be a great meal for one person, and 3-4 is enough for two people.

data.title: Finally did brunch again after a long time since last brunch we had there
data.text: Went with wife for brunch and she got a special of rope tostadas and I got a cuban benedict.  Both were so good I ate all of mine and some of my wife's  and hadn't been that full for a while.  Great meal and we had a great time with good weather which never hurts either.

data.title: Very good cuban/tapas/general Latin cuisine!
data.text: Good, reliable, consistent. Good service, nice live music occasionally. Overall, it's one of my favorite spots in GNV. The food is also child friendly!

data.title: Interesting and fresh
data.text:
Emiliano's seems to change radically every few years,  both the décor and the menu.  
The menu items are not consistently good, but the fish dishes are almost always wonderful.  I always enjoy the tapas and of course the desserts.  To me it just seems like the potential is there, but often the reality doesn't quite measure up.  Gainesville has a thriving Latin American population which should provide the basis for high quality Latin dining experience.

data.title: Lovely place
data.text: Nice pre hurricane breeze, so we sat outside. Service was great and food was delicious. Price was reasonable and went home with plenty of left overs.

data.title: Absolutely wonder brunch. Always love this place.
data.text: Got the crab stuffed avocado dish. Absolutely wonderful. Everything always is when we dine here. Mimosas and Bloody Mary's are delicious as well.

data.title: Great Family Style Cuban Reataurant
data.text:
I am very picky with Hispanic food especially fast foods like Chipotle, Taco bells, Moes and such which are all horrible I don't eat there Those are all peasant food places from poor countries.  However and good Hispanic restaurant cannot be beat.  It's all home made and Emiliano's in Gainesville has real food.  You will not find tacos, burritos then you will find what Hispanic food is all about.  It is not necessary to add hot spices to Hispanic food to make it good.  So my favorite is arroz con pollo so try it out when visiting or going to a Gator football game.

Most people don't know what good Hispanic food really is except maybe in more cosmopolitan cities.  So if you can handle reality try the real thing.

data.title: Good Choice
data.text: I would recommend Emiliano's for something different from the norm.  I had the pork shank which I would definitely recommend.  Very friendly staff and overall a good experience.

data.title: Excellent Sunday Brunch in Downtown
data.text: This was a perfect spot for Sunday Brunch.  Not only was my meal plated beautifully, it was delicious.  The layer of flavors was well thought out. I will definitely eat here again.

data.title: Pretty good Tapas and a tasty Mojito
data.text:
We went here for a business dinner and found out we were within their "Happy hour" window by 10
Minutes. We ordered several Tapas dishes - crabcakes,empanadas- and also tried their Mojito and sangria. Good value and tapas choices were pretty good. I'd recommend this place. Only downside of sitting outside was the inebriated man that stopped at our table and interrupted our conversation to ask for money to buy beer.

data.title: Great for large group or small family meal (really great food)
data.text: With 3 daughters at UF, we get to experience many options for food when we visit, but our dinner at Emiliano's Cafe was one of the best to date.  Six different entres were ordered at our table and each person was sure that theirs was the best.  The service was average, but cordial and we didn't have to wait so these are positives.  One of our daughters had been here recently as an end of Summer Internship dinner with many of her coworkers and she indicated they had a great experience that evening as well.  They do great Mexican food, but they have non-mexican options as well.

data.title: Good menu for vegetarians
data.text: Latin fusion.  Great service, comfortable place.  We sat outside because the air conditioning was a little strong for us (not being Floridians, we're not used to it). We ordered a real cross-section from the menu and vegetarians, vegans, pescatarians and meat-eaters all were satisfied.

data.title: New favorite spot
data.text: I've already posted once, but I just don't know if I did this place justice. My wife and I were here a couple months ago for date night and loved it. This past trip we went with friends for brunch. Wow! $5 bloody Marie's, and $3 mimosas. Can't beat it. As for the food...I can't make this stuff up. It's so delicious! See my pictures. They have some of the most amazing sounding food. My friend and I went with the mojo Benedict. Loved it! My wife had the French toast. Loved it! And our other friend had the Cuban Benedict...you guessed it. Loved it! The cooks do a phenomenal job. This place is a little more pricey than some, but well worth it. You truly get what you pay for here.

data.title: Good Cuban Sandwich
data.text: Went to lunch here on a Saturday.  Very busy.  Service and food were both excellent.  My sister had the blackened Grouper Tacos and I had the Cuban Sandwich.

data.title: Second visit even better than the first!
data.text: Best paella I have ever had. I first visited here back in April and loved it and was anxious to return. It did not disappoint. Husband had the pork shank which he said was delicious. Son had a chicken dish with a jalapeno sauce he said was great. Excellent service.

data.title: Not your typical cuban restaurant
data.text: We went to Emiliano's for breakfast thinking it was your typical cuban/latin restaurant, it is not! I had a wrap with scrambled eggs and chorizo with salsa, black beans and sour cream on top and it was really good just not the typical cuban/latin breakfast. The service was good as well.

data.title: My new favorite Gainesville Restaurant
data.text: I will definitely return to Emiliano's.  The wait staff is excellent: Our server knew the specials backwards and forwards, and was able to make recommendations based on questions he asked us.  He also recommended wines and perfect desserts.  Our meals were extremely good.  Our party of 5 ordered a wide variety of entrees.  Each was excellent.  The atmosphere at Emiliano's can be described as 'high-end, but comfortable'.  We felt welcome and appreciated.  Definitely a new favorite!

data.title: Great lunch
data.text: Went for lunch, found the prices excellent,service excellent, portions substantial and quality exceptional.. Would highly this to anyone in the area

data.title: Great tapas!
data.text: Emiliano's menu is delicious. The atmosphere is great and the food quality is really good. I would definitely recommend this place.
